    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-05T21:03:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-05T21:03:00-05:00" n="553"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3368</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_TAR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thomson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d553fn1">Sent via the Legation in China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Irkutsk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-06T09:00:00+06:57">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1918, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 9, 9.35 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Controversy between <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> government not yet ended, and feeling
                    of all classes Russians this district very bitter against <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> and his mercenary troops, who are
                    regarded as hirelings of Japan. <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName>
                    desires supreme authority over eastern Siberia, which territory is coveted by
                    Japan as sphere of influence. General feeling is that <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName>’s [policies?] are dictated by Japanese
                    military officers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TAR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
